Chu Xia! Your utility bill
is three days in arrears!

60
00:02:42,570 --> 00:02:44,210
I'll cut it off!

61
00:02:44,210 --> 00:02:45,000
Alright!

62
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:46,580
I'll pay for it!

63
00:02:46,610 --> 00:02:49,170
Chu Xia, stop!

64
00:02:51,520 --> 00:02:53,310
It's hard to make money.

65
00:02:53,320 --> 00:02:55,440
Moreover, there are monsters around.

66
00:02:55,490 --> 00:02:57,970
Such as Chicken Wings Angela.

67
00:03:07,290 --> 00:03:09,470
Get out of the way!

68
00:03:09,580 --> 00:03:11,370
Promise me to stop working

69
00:03:11,440 --> 00:03:13,840
in Feng Shao's salon from now on.

70
00:03:14,150 --> 00:03:15,530
Then I'll let you go.

71
00:03:16,580 --> 00:03:19,060
Neither you nor me

72
00:03:19,140 --> 00:03:21,490
can make the call.

73
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:22,460
An Chu Xia!

74
00:03:22,540 --> 00:03:24,560
You are getting more aggressive now.

75
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:29,300
The man who appears

76
00:03:29,310 --> 00:03:30,570
in flashes and smokes

77
00:03:30,580 --> 00:03:33,636
with his own background music
is Feng Shao, the deputy head

78
00:03:33,661 --> 00:03:36,924
of Huo Ni Hall in Cat Ears Lane.

79
00:03:37,540 --> 00:03:38,440
Feng Shao.

80
00:03:46,860 --> 00:03:49,980
Chu Xia, it's important to make money.

81
00:03:51,700 --> 00:03:54,510
Go first and leave it to me.

82
00:03:54,580 --> 00:03:57,300
Alright, I'll treat you milk later.

83
00:04:01,330 --> 00:04:03,310
You are trying to protect her!

84
00:04:10,930 --> 00:04:13,680
Come on, you are a girl.

85
00:04:14,240 --> 00:04:16,190
Why do you always mess with her?

86
00:04:16,760 --> 00:04:18,150
I've told you many times.

87
00:04:18,520 --> 00:04:20,770
Don't mess with Chu Xia!

88
00:04:20,900 --> 00:04:21,940
But you're stubborn.

89
00:05:18,765 --> 00:05:20,265
[Master Devil Do Not Kiss Me S1]

90
00:05:22,705 --> 00:05:23,705
[Episode 1]

91
00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:30,320
In every girl's princess dream,
there's always a prince

92
00:05:30,360 --> 00:05:32,000
riding on a white horse.

93
00:05:32,030 --> 00:05:34,520
Smart, chivalrous and courteous.

94
00:05:34,870 --> 00:05:38,880
As exquisite as an artwork.

95
00:05:39,980 --> 00:05:43,140
Apparently, he's not the prince.

96
00:05:43,330 --> 00:05:46,890
He's a demon like the
mumbler Monk Xuanzang.

97
00:05:51,730 --> 00:05:52,930
I have to go.

98
00:05:55,960 --> 00:05:58,790
I'm afraid that you can't go now.

99
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:01,750
Ask him to come over.

100
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:03,120
I'll teach him a lesson.

101
00:06:04,020 --> 00:06:05,970
If he doesn't show up today...

102
00:06:14,790 --> 00:06:15,930
What are you looking at?

103
00:06:16,290 --> 00:06:18,260
Didn't you see we're arguing?

104
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:19,900
Do you know how much I love you?

105
00:06:20,080 --> 00:06:21,700
Be it one or two years,

106
00:06:21,710 --> 00:06:22,870
a decade or a century,

107
00:06:22,880 --> 00:06:23,920
I love you for ten thousand years

108
00:06:23,950 --> 00:06:25,250
and ten thousand light years.

109
00:06:25,280 --> 00:06:27,760
The light year is a unit of
length instead of time.

110
00:06:28,210 --> 00:06:29,990
It is the distance whereby

111
00:06:29,990 --> 00:06:31,870
the speed of light times a year.

112
00:06:31,940 --> 00:06:35,930
The speed of light is 299,792,458 m/s.

113
00:06:36,060 --> 00:06:38,050
By assuming 365.25 days as a year,

114
00:06:38,080 --> 00:06:40,530
One light-year is about
9.4 trillion kilometres.

115
00:06:40,710 --> 00:06:43,060
This is the correct
interpretation of light years

116
00:06:44,050 --> 00:06:46,300
and the distance between you two.

117
00:06:48,520 --> 00:06:49,800
Who are you?

118
00:06:50,690 --> 00:06:51,940
Go away!

119
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:09,980
Bro, are you okay?

120
00:07:10,080 --> 00:07:10,780
I'm fine.

121
00:07:11,280 --> 00:07:13,790
Why did you pop out then?

122
00:07:13,810 --> 00:07:14,630
For fun?

123
00:07:14,770 --> 00:07:16,690
You spilled the milk! Are you blind?

124
00:07:16,740 --> 00:07:17,770
Pay for it!

125
00:07:18,850 --> 00:07:19,550
It's him!

126
00:07:19,650 --> 00:07:22,360
He kicked me out, he should pay for it!

127
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:27,350
Thank you.

128
00:07:32,170 --> 00:07:33,320
Stop!

129
00:07:33,900 --> 00:07:36,460
Stop! Are you deaf?

130
00:08:11,610 --> 00:08:13,700
Anything wrong with my mouth?

131
00:08:14,330 --> 00:08:15,770
